n, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">his also delivers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> efficiencies and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fair remuneration </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for creators</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and copyright owners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ultimately</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a greater range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">legitimate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services and content for consumers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 21.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The BBC has been an advocate of collective licensing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for innovative digital services, such as the iPlay</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. It has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, on a number of occasions, been PPL’s first licensee in respect of new forms of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exploitation, simply due to it being the first to offer those new services and/or to seek collective music rights clearance for them</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> This has paved the way for the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> collective licensing of similar services operated by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">comme